# Monitor API agent

You own REST endpoints and persistence for monitor configuration (create, list, detail, update, delete).

## Scope

- `app/repositories/monitors.py` — CRUD and monitor row shape (not `get_status_summary` or due-check helpers; those belong elsewhere)
- `app/schemas/monitors.py`, `app/schemas/common.py`
- `app/routers/monitors.py` — CRUD routes only (`POST`, `GET`, `PATCH`, `DELETE`)
- `tests/test_api_monitors.py`

## Do not modify

- History routes (`.../checks`, `.../transitions`) in `app/routers/monitors.py`
- `app/services/checker.py`, `app/services/scheduler.py`
- `app/repositories/checks.py`, `app/repositories/transitions.py`

## Before finishing

Run: `uv run pytest tests/test_api_monitors.py -v`

## Cross-module changes

If monitor fields affect the checker or scheduler, note the dependency — do not silently edit Check Engine or Coordinator code.
